      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Night Bush Presented Himself to America</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anthony Mancini letter seconds Sanford Levinson's Aug 4 Op-Ed article on dubious constitutionality of George W Bush's selection of Dick Cheney as his running mate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''2 Texans, Not 1'' (Op-Ed, Aug. 4): Sanford Levinson's thought-provoking article highlighting the dubious constitutionality of George W. Bush's selection of Dick Cheney as his running mate raises another interesting question that was not explored.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''2 Texans, Not 1'' (Op-Ed, Aug. 4): Sanford Levinson's thought-provoking article highlighting the dubious constitutionality of George W. Bush's selection of Dick Cheney as his running mate raises another interesting question that was not explored.</p>
        <p>If the Republican ticket wins in November, with the Texas electors voting for it, might this not instigate a lawsuit by some interested party challenging the legality of the contest? The prospect is disquieting, especially in the wake of the constitutional crisis over the impeachment of President Clinton.</p>
        <p>ANTHONY MANCINI  New York, Aug. 4, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is director of the journalism program at Brooklyn College.</p>
      </block>
